title: Best hotel and unparallel hospitality
text: My partner and I stayed at Caldera premium villas for 6 days/5 nights. We checked-in almost midnight on the first day. It has been a long day for us due to our flight being delayed from Athens for 4hrs. We were met by a staff in the drop off location and carried our large luggages all the way down to the hotel. We weren't really happy with the room given to us simply because it's all the way down and there's alot of stairs to maneuver and my partner's knees were acting up and bothering her. We talked to Karla in the reception the following morning to see if she can transfer us in a higher room. We are even ready to downgrade to a room without a hot tub which we booked. Karla was so understanding and helped us transfer to a room with the same category. We really enjoyed our stay in this hotel. The location is perfect with the magnificent view of the caldera and just a walk away from all the restaurants and shops in Oia. All the hotel staff are very accomodating and friendly. Overall rating on this vacation: EXTRAORDINARY!

title: Beautiful Accommodations
text: I checked in with the sweetest young man! Some reviews suggested that the staff were rude. Not the case for me. Lovely conversation and all my questions were answered. My room was ready and it was beautiful. Not sure about some of the negative reviews I had read  about the conditions of the rooms. It was clean, well stocked with toiletries, coffee, mini fridge and microwave. Extremely comfortable and quiet. I would suggest bringing your own bath towels. The towels aren‚Äôt large enough for an adult. The breakfast was good, eggs, sausage, potatoes, coffee, fruit and packaged sweet treats. The area was quiet and close to many attractions. I walked to the Fountain of Youth and the Trolley Tour & Old Jail was literally a 10-15 walk. Loved hearing the peacocks singing during the day.  Perfect location to everything! My much needed getaway provided me with a wonderful experience!
